    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>An American Town Meeting: The Issue Is Race</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Rosemary Bothwell letter welcomes June 4 article in series How Race Is Lived in America, so that 'each of us can see the hurt and pain that African-Americans endure daily'</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''How Race Is Lived in America'' (front page, June 4):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''How Race Is Lived in America'' (front page, June 4):</p>
        <p>Your yearlong study of the daily encounters between the races in schools, streets, churches, movies and sports arenas is to me very much needed so each of us can see the hurt and pain that African-Americans endure daily.</p>
        <p>ROSEMARY BOTHWELL  Jenkintown, Pa., June 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
